Today the International Mobile Festival “Cinema in the Service of the Fatherland” starts in Moscow. From February 19 to 22, the largest venues in the capital, including the Victory Museum, will show feature films and documentaries about those who dedicated their lives to serving their native land. The extensive program was compiled with the participation of the festival director, director Olesya Shigina.

February 19: 9 film works will be presented at the Victory Museum, screenings will be held in the Vasilevsky and Rokossovsky halls; 14:00 - in the Kauchuk center of Sechenov University, director Olesya Shigina will present her new film “Brave. Moms"; 19:00 - the opening of the interactive platform of the Committee of the Families of Soldiers of the Fatherland "Development of Regional Cinema" will take place at the Illusion cinema. Member of the RF OP Alexander Malkevich, presenter of the Union TV channel (DPR) Alexandra Lazareva, as well as members of the SVO will speak at the opening. February 20: 12:00 - the world premiere of the documentary film “Unarmed” (dir. . Manuchehr Ramezani);14:00 - a special screening of the film “Holy Archipelago” directed by Sergei Debizhev and a creative meeting with him will take place there;18:00 - the official Opening Ceremony of the International Festival will begin in pavilion No. 57 “Russia - My History” at VDNKh. February 21: 10:30 - competitive screenings of films from festival participants will be held at the Victory Museum on Poklonnaya Hill; 12:30 - an interactive platform of the Committee of the Families of Soldiers of the Fatherland and the Union of Fathers of Russia “Father. Father's house. Fatherland" with film presentations; 18:00 - in the Kauchuk center of Sechenov University - the premiere of the film "At the Edge of the Abyss" by military documentarian Max Fadeev. February 22: 15:00 - in the Sber pavilion at VDNKh there will be a presentation of film projects of novice authors " Baptism of fire";
18.00 18.00 - the closing ceremony of the festival will take place in pavilion No. 57 “Russia - My History” at VDNKh. You can familiarize yourself with the festival program and register for the events here. Admission is free.📮Subscribe to LOMOVKA

